{"name": "z0z-tools", "metadata": {"name": "Z0Z-tools", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "packaging", "resampy", "soundfile"], "summary": "Audio processing, data structure, and package management tools.", "upload_time": 1732796142}, "documentation": ["# Z0Z_tools\n\n\"Z0Z_\"- is a placeholder, and a Z0Z_tool is at best, a prototype.\n\n## Do you also get irritated by \"'true' is invalid and stupid. Did you mean 'True'?\"\n\n`oopsieKwargsie()` will try to interpret an errant parameter value as `True`, `False`, or `None`.\n\n## Allow a calling function to limit concurrency to a ratio, absolute count, or relative count with `defineConcurrencyLimit()`\n\n## Install an arbitrary package with `pipAnything`\n\nTry to install a package that doesn't have installation files.\n\n```sh\npython -m Z0Z_tools.pipAnything <pathPackage>\n```\n\n## Unpack and convert elements to `str` types with `stringItUp()`\n\n## Merge and/or lightly clean a dictionary of lists with `updateExtendPolishDictionaryLists()`\n\n- Merges multiple dictionaries of lists into a single dictionary.\n- Optionally remove duplicates each list.\n- Optionally sort each list.\n- Optionally delete data that won't merge.\n\n## Easily read/write WAV files with `readAudioFile()` and `writeWav()`\n\nThe only option is the sample rate.\n\n## Use `loadWaveforms()` to create one array of waveforms from multiple files\n\n## Install this package\n\n```sh\npip install Z0Z-tools\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "unittests.test_pipAnything", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "unittests.test_pipAnything.TestPipAnything", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "unittests.test_pipAnything.TestPipAnything.test_makeListRequirementsFromRequirementsFile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Test the makeListRequirementsFromRequirementsFile function."]}, {"name": "unittests.test_pipAnything.TestPipAnything.test_make_setupDOTpy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Test the make_setupDOTpy function."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile.setUp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile.test_read_mono_audio_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile.test_read_stereo_audio_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile.test_read_audio_file_resampling", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestReadAudioFile.test_invalid_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestLoadWaveforms", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestLoadWaveforms.setUp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "unittests.test_ioAudio.TestLoadWav